{"word":"H4720 - מִקְדָּשׁ - miqdâsh - mik-dawsh' - Chapel","slug":"H4720","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">מִקְדָּשׁ</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>miqdâsh"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>mik-dawsh'"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Chapel"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x05DE;&#x05E7;&#x05BC;&#x05D3;&#x05E9;&#x05C1;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&#x05DE;&#x05E7;&#x05D3;&#x05BC;&#x05E9;&#x05C1; - miqda&#x0302;sh  miqq<sup>e</sup>da&#x0302;sh</b> - <i>mik-dawsh', mik-ked-awsh'</i><p/>From <a href=\"#/H6942\">H6942</a>; a <i>consecrated</i> thing or place, especially a <i>palace</i>, <i>sanctuary</i> (whether of Jehovah or of idols) or <i>asylum: - </i>chapel, hallowed part, holy place, sanctuary."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H6918\">H6918</a>, <a href=\"#/H6942\">H6942</a>, <a href=\"#/H6943\">H6943</a>, <a href=\"#/H6944\">H6944</a>, <a href=\"#/H6945\">H6945</a>, <a href=\"#/H6946\">H6946</a>, <a href=\"#/H6947\">H6947</a>, <a href=\"#/H6948\">H6948</a>"}]}